    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>HONG KONG TAXI FUEL</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Mark Landler</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Landler, Mark</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Hong Kong government announces measures to convert nearly all of city's 18,000 taxis from diesel fuel to liquefied petroleum gas by end of 2001; diesel-powered taxis are major cause of smog that hangs over Hong Kong on most days; measures range from eliminating duty on liquefied petroleum gas to giving taxi drivers grants to buy cars that use cleaner-burning fuel; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The Hong Kong govern-ment announced measures to convert nearly all of the city's 18,000 taxis from diesel fuel to liquefied petroleum gas by the end of 2001. Diesel-powered taxis are a major cause of the smog that hangs over Hong Kong on most days. The measures range from eliminating the duty on liquefied petroleum gas to giving taxi drivers grants to buy cars that use the cleaner-burning fuel.</p>
        <p>Mark Landler</p>
      </block>
